# 🔒 STRICT IMPLEMENTATION ADDENDUM (NO AMBIGUITY)

This document overrides any vague interpretation. All requirements below are **mandatory**.

---

# 1. DATA PERSISTENCE (MANDATORY)

## ✅ REQUIREMENT

The model **MUST store results from EVERY simulation iteration** inside the adaptive loop.

### REQUIRED DATA STRUCTURES

```netlogo
globals [
  durations          ;; list of conflict durations per run
  outcomes           ;; list of 1 (British win) or 0 (loss)
]
```

---

## ✅ PER-ITERATION RECORDING (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

After EACH simulation completes:

```netlogo
if british-win? [
  set outcomes lput 1 outcomes
] [
  set outcomes lput 0 outcomes
]

set durations lput conflict-duration durations
```

---

## ❗ WHY THIS IS REQUIRED

* Needed for:

  * mean
  * variance
  * standard deviation
  * confidence intervals
* Without storing all values → **statistically invalid**

---

# 2. SIMULATION TERMINATION (INNER LOOP)

## ✅ REQUIREMENT

A **single simulation run MUST terminate ONLY when a battle outcome is reached**

---

## ✅ EXACT LOGIC (NO INTERPRETATION)

```netlogo
to-report simulation-over?
  report (
    (not any? argentine-troops) OR
    (all? argentine-troops [surrendered?])
  ) OR
  (not any? british-troops)
end
```

---

## ✅ OUTCOME DEFINITION (MANDATORY)

### British Victory:

* All Argentine troops:

  * dead OR
  * surrendered

```netlogo
to-report british-win?
  report (
    (not any? argentine-troops) OR
    (all? argentine-troops [surrendered?])
  )
end
```

---

### British Loss:

* All British troops eliminated

---

## ❗ CRITICAL

* Simulation MUST NOT stop early
* Simulation MUST NOT stop based on time unless explicitly modeled

---

# 3. EXPERIMENT TERMINATION (OUTER LOOP)

## ✅ REQUIREMENT

The adaptive experiment stops ONLY when:

```netlogo
(runs > 30) AND (moe < target-moe)
```

---

## ✅ EXACT MOE FORMULA

```netlogo
set p-hat mean outcomes

set moe z-score * sqrt((p-hat * (1 - p-hat)) / runs)
```

---

## ✅ SAFETY CAP (MANDATORY)

```netlogo
if runs >= max-runs [
  stop
]
```

---

# 4. RANDOMNESS (STRICT REQUIREMENT)

Each simulation MUST be independent.

### REQUIRED:

```netlogo
random-seed new-seed
```

placed INSIDE `setup-simulation`

---

## ❗ FAILURE MODE

If omitted:

* identical runs
* invalid confidence intervals
* meaningless results

---

# 5. STRICT FUNCTION SEPARATION

## ❗ MUST FOLLOW THIS STRUCTURE

| Function              | Purpose                  |
| --------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `setup`               | Initialize experiment    |
| `setup-simulation`    | Reset ONLY per-run state |
| `go-step`             | One tick of simulation   |
| `go-until-end`        | Runs ONE battle          |
| `run-until-converged` | Runs MANY battles        |

---

## ❗ HARD RULE

```text
NEVER call setup inside run loop
ONLY call setup-simulation
```

---

